<h1>AMNI-CORE</h1>
<p class="desc">QUANTUM-SAFE SYSTEMS PLATFORM &bull; GPU-FORWARD &bull; POST-LEGACY ARCHITECTURE</p>
</div>
<section>
<h2>BUILT TO REPLACE, NOT TO PATCH</h2>
<p style="text-align:center;color:var(--dim);max-width:700px;margin:0 auto 2rem;font-size:.9rem">A ground-up systems platform designed for the post-quantum era. No legacy compatibility layers. No inherited attack surfaces. GPU-native execution from boot to application layer. A fundamentally different approach to how machines compute.</p>
<div class="features">
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128737;</div>
<h4>QUANTUM-SAFE</h4>
<p>Every cryptographic primitive, key exchange, and integrity mechanism is designed to withstand known quantum computing attack vectors. No retrofit — built quantum-resistant from day one.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#9889;</div>
<h4>GPU-FORWARD</h4>
<p>Compute pipeline treats the GPU as a first-class execution target, not an accelerator. Scheduling, memory management, and I/O are designed around massively parallel hardware.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128272;</div>
<h4>PROPRIETARY ENCODING</h4>
<p>Novel computational encoding architecture that operates at a fundamentally different numerical and symbolic level than conventional systems. Internal representation is unlike any existing platform.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128640;</div>
<h4>HARDWARE ISOLATION</h4>
<p>Memory model enforces isolation at the hardware boundary. Process separation is physical, not virtual. Side-channel attack surface reduced by architectural design.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128736;</div>
<h4>ZERO LEGACY</h4>
<p>No POSIX. No Win32. No inherited syscall surface. Every interface designed for current and next-generation hardware with no backward-compatibility burden.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#9877;</div>
<h4>INTEGRITY BY DEFAULT</h4>
<p>Boot chain, kernel, and every loaded module are integrity-verified before execution. Tamper detection is systemic, not optional.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section>
<h2>DESIGN PRINCIPLES</h2>
<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>POST-LEGACY</h3>
<p>Modern operating systems carry decades of backward-compatible abstractions. Amni-Core starts from a clean sheet — no emulation layers, no compatibility shims, no inherited vulnerabilities.</p>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>GPU-NATIVE PIPELINE</h3>
<p>Traditional OS architectures treat GPUs as peripheral devices. Amni-Core integrates GPU compute into the core execution model, enabling parallel-first scheduling across the entire system stack.</p>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>NOVEL COMPUTATION</h3>
<p>The platform employs a proprietary encoding and computation model that diverges from conventional binary-centric architectures. Implementation details are classified as trade secrets.</p>
</div>
<div class="card">
<h3>QUANTUM RESILIENCE</h3>
<p>All system-level cryptographic operations use primitives resistant to Shor's algorithm and Grover's algorithm. Key sizes, hash functions, and signature schemes are selected for post-quantum security margins.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section>
<h2>SPECIFICATIONS</h2>
<table class="spec-table">
<tr><th>PARAMETER</th><th>VALUE</th></tr>
<tr><td>Architecture</td><td>Proprietary (non-POSIX, non-NT)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Execution Model</td><td>GPU-forward parallel pipeline</td></tr>
<tr><td>Encoding</td><td>Proprietary computational encoding</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cryptography</td><td>Post-quantum safe (all primitives)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Memory Model</td><td>Hardware-enforced isolation</td></tr>
<tr><td>Boot Security</td><td>Full integrity chain verification</td></tr>
<tr><td>Legacy Support</td><td>None by design</td></tr>
<tr><td>Target Hardware</td><td>Desktop / Embedded (GPU-equipped)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Status</td><td>Active development</td></tr>
</table>
</section>
<section style="text-align:center">
<h2>STATUS</h2>
<p style="color:var(--dim);margin-bottom:2rem;font-size:.9rem;max-width:600px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto">Amni-Core is in active development. This is a long-horizon project building toward a fundamentally new computing platform. Updates will be published as development milestones are reached.</p>
